The official language in Sofia is Bulgarian. It is based on the Bulgarian, so-called Cyrillic alphabet. Bulgaria is the only country in the world that has its holiday of literacy, education and culture. It is celebrated every year on 24 May, when Bulgaria honours the work of the holy brotherd Cyril and Methodius who devised the alphabet. Nowadays the Cyrillic alphabet is used not only by Bulgarians, but by Serbs, Montenegrins, Russians, Ukrainians, Belarusians, as well as by non-Slavic peoples like Mongols. A total of over 200 million people! With the accession of Bulgaria to the European Union on 1 January 2007, the Cyrillic alphabet became one of the official alphabets in the community.


Bellow you will find some common Bulgarian words and phrases:


Welcome: Добре дошъл (Dobre doshal);

Hello: Здравейте (Zdravejte);

Pleased to meet you: Радвам се да се запознаем (Radvam se da se zapoznaem);

Good morning: Добро утро (Dobro utro);

Good afternoon: Добър ден (Dobar den);

Good evening: Добър вечер (Dobar vecher);

Good night: Лека нощ (Leka nost);

Goodbye: Довиждане (Dovigdane) or Чао (Chao);

Thank you: Благодаря ви (Blagodarya vi);

How much is this?: Колко струва това? (Kolko struva tova?);

Please: Моля (Molja);

Sorry: Съжалявам! (Sagaliavam);

Excuse me: Извинявам се (Izvinjavam se);

How are you?: Как си? (Kak si?);



Days and expressions of time:


Monday: Понеделник (Ponedelnik);

Tuesday: Вторник (Vtornik);

Wednesday: Сряда (Sriada);

Thursday: Четвъртък (Chetvartak);

Friday: Петък (Petak);

Saturday: Събота (Sabota);

Sunday: Неделя (Nedelya);

Today: Днес (Dnes);

Tomorrow: Утре (Utre);

Yesterday: Вчера (Vchera);



Restaurant vocabulary:


The bill: Сметката (Smetkata);

To drink: Да пия (Da piya);

To eat: Да ям (Da yam);

Cheers: Наздраве! (Nazdrave);

Water: Водa (Voda);

Wine: Вино (Vino);

Beer: Бира (Bira);

Bread: Хляб (Hliab);

Dessert: Десерт (Desert);

Meat: Месо (Meso);

Fish: Риба (Riba);

Fruit: Плод (Plod);

Vegetable: Зеленчук (Zelenchuk);

Ice cream: Сладолед (Sladoled);

Have a nice meal: Добър апетит (Dobar apetit);


Other languages:


Many residents of Sofia understand English, Russian, German, French and Spanish. A lot of restaurants have menus in other languages and public transport sings are also in English.

Sofia has a modern city transport network that serves the entire city. The main operator is Sofia Urban Mobility Center. The company has a large fleet of 535 buses, 93 trolleybuses and 156 trams which pass throughout the city. Metropoliten is the municipality-owned company that operates the Sofia Metro with 26 trainsets on 2 lines.


TICKETS 
Single travel ticket – 1 BGN;

Single travel ticket from the driver – 1 BGN;

Single travel ticket from the ticket vending machine in trolleys and trams – 1 BGN;

Single travel ticket from the ticket vending machine or the ticket office in the metro – for the metro – 1 BGN;

Electronic ticket for ten travels for one passenger loaded in electronic card, tor trams and trolleys – 8 BGN;

Electronic ticket for ten travels, loaded in electronic card, for metro – 8 BGN;


Important: Any piece of baggage exceeding 60х40х40 cm requires a separate ticket.



METRO


Single trip card - Price: 1,00 BGN.

The card is issued by Transport Documents Machine at the entrances of the metro or by a cashier at the cash-desks of "Metropoliten" JSC and is validated at the validator located on the barriers to the metro entrance. The card can be used for entrance to the metro up tp 30 minutes after its issuance.



Electronic card for 10 single trips Price: 8,00 BGN.


Charging the electronic card issued and loaded by "Metropoliten" JSC takes place at the validators located at the barriers to entry in the metro. Anytime when charging the card the number of remaining trips are reduced by one. E-cards are purchased and their value is 1.00 BGN VAT including. Each e-card has a 3 year validity from the date of its first refueling of trips in the system.



CARDS



Daily - for evey line of the city public transport - Price: 4,00 BGN. 
Monthly - for metro - Price: 35,00 BGN. (customized); 42,00 BGN. (non customized) 
Paper and e-cards can be issued by each cash-desks of the metro stations.
